<item>
            <title>[MNG-4238] Custom ArtifactHandler provided by build extension isn&apos;t used for project artifact</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MNG-4238</link>
                <project id="12316922" key="MNG">Maven (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If I reference a build extension which provides a custom ArtifactHandler, then set the packaging for the project so that it should use the custom ArtifactHandler when it installs, I find that a default on-demand ArtifactHandler is used instead.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looking at this more closely, it appears that ArtifactHandlers brought in by extensions (NOT plugins with extensions == true) are never registered with the already-loaded ArtifactHandlerManager. Since Maven &amp;lt; 3.0 doesn&apos;t support dynamic collections of components which would detect and include the new extension handler, these handlers are never used.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
