                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14415258" author="gdogaru" created="Tue, 1 Sep 2009 09:58:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am using maven 2.2.1 and I have the same problem for a custom ArtifactHandler define by the plugin that provides estensions.&lt;br/&gt;
When I use in my mojo @requiresDependencyResolution test  and i call projects.artifacts it gets all the artifacts for test(including junit &amp;amp; others) but not my custom artifact type.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14415290" author="jdcasey" created="Tue, 1 Sep 2009 10:14:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You have to set &amp;lt;extensions&amp;gt;true&amp;lt;/extensions&amp;gt; on the plugin that provides the artifact handler, or it won&apos;t be loaded.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you&apos;re still experiencing the problem with extensions enabled, please see if you can provide a failing test case so we can verify/track down the problem and fix it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14415221" author="gdogaru" created="Wed, 2 Sep 2009 02:37:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am using &amp;lt;extensions&amp;gt;true&amp;lt;/extensions&amp;gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This happens if I use @requiresDependencyResolution test and my dependency has test scope. If I use compile for the dependency scope the artifact appears in the list of projects artifacts.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17999165" author="JIRAUSER302100" created="Sat, 5 Jul 2025 18:46:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This project has moved from Jira to GitHub Issues. This issue was migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven/issues/5921&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;apache/maven#5921&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
